    {
      "id": "wOO9R97C2e5MKeCteChtz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1935.792265864853,
      "y": 8654.734531625078,
      "width": 2182.967529296875,
      "height": 810,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#e6fcf5",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bFM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1071005014,
      "version": 953,
      "versionNonce": 1570598282,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769798448785,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In setting.py , django provide builtin middleware already like SecurityMiddleware, Authentication Middleware, CSRF middleware\n and so on. these already called in every request, we can add our own custom middleware as well.\n\n\nHow we can create Custom Middleware -> \n\n1 create 1 folder of any name like middleware inside our root folder\n2 create __init__.py inside middleware folder\n3 create any file like custom_middleware.py\n4 write our logic inside using         \n             init -> constructor, \n            process_request -> before urls.py hit, \n            process_view -> before views.py hit, \n            process_response -> after views.py, \n            process_exception -> for exception\nand so on..\n\n      ",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In setting.py , django provide builtin middleware already like SecurityMiddleware, Authentication Middleware, CSRF middleware\n and so on. these already called in every request, we can add our own custom middleware as well.\n\n\nHow we can create Custom Middleware -> \n\n1 create 1 folder of any name like middleware inside our root folder\n2 create __init__.py inside middleware folder\n3 create any file like custom_middleware.py\n4 write our logic inside using         \n             init -> constructor, \n            process_request -> before urls.py hit, \n            process_view -> before views.py hit, \n            process_response -> after views.py, \n            process_exception -> for exception\nand so on..\n\n      ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
